Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces.

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Trim, peel, and quarter @carrots{9%ounce}(trimmed, peeled, and quartered lengthwise); thinly slice crosswise into quarter-moons.

Heat a drizzle of oil and half the @sesame oil{1%tablespoon} in a small #pot{} (use all the sesame oil and a medium pot for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 1 cup water (2 cups for 4), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until Step 6.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrots and a pinch of salt; stir to combine. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Uncover and add @peas{4%ounce} and 1/4 cup water (1/2 cup for 4 servings). Cook until carrots and peas are tender and water has completely evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a #plate{}.

When cauliflower is almost done roasting, combine @katsu sauce{4%tablespoon}, @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, 1 tsp water (2 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}.

Microwave until warmed, ~{20-30%seconds}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Transfer roasted cauliflower to bowl with sauce; toss to combine.

To pot with rice, add carrots and peas and half the scallion greens. Stir to combine; taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} and top with glazed cauliflower. Sprinkle with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and remaining scallion greens. Serve.

> This vegan dinner idea is one balanced flavor bomb of a meal, thanks to some of our favorite umami-rich condiments. Crisp-roasted cauliflower is coated in a velvety blend of hoisin, katsu sauce, and sweet Thai chili sauce—a combination that's hard to beat! Fragrant fried rice, bejeweled with tender-crisp carrots and sweet peas, is the perfect bed for nestling the savory-sweet glazed cauliflower. Finish with a sprinkle of scallion greens and nutty sesame seeds for crunchy contrast.